  "name": "creditTransaction",
  "domain": "MultiCreditTransaction",
  "operationType": "CREATE",
  "invocationType": [
    "SYNC"
  ],
  "description": [
    "This service orchestrates a multi-credit transaction creation by routing through a series of validation, enrichment, and preparation stages based on the detected feature type (FundTransfer, MultiCreditTransaction, MultiDebitTransaction, OpenAccount, AccountClosure, or TDAccountPreClosure). It begins by validating the incoming request payload using rules-engine-driven checks, throwing structured validation exceptions for any failing fields such as currency, amount, account number, or transaction line integrity. Once validated, the service fetches the relevant deposit account records and retrieves the corresponding customer and account contracts, enriching each transaction leg with contract details and deposit amounts; if any contract is missing or invalid, the flow terminates with an application exception. For credit-eligible legs, it checks whether credit is permitted against the account's contract terms, and then evaluates multi-leg transaction limits via a limit evaluation utility, storing any external reference IDs for potential downstream reversal. The service also determines fee applicability per leg based on the feature type and applicable fee configurations, then prepares the persistence context by mapping DTOs to entities, injecting fee-applicable accounts into the command payload, and setting the appropriate process state (e.g. MULTI_CREDIT_WITH_FEE_INITIATED) before delegating the finalised command to an external system handler to complete the transaction."
  ],
